        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-06-06 21:40:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm happy with this landing ASAP if it fixes the interoperability with 1.8.6+64bit_hash clients against 2.1 servers.\n\nWe still need to do some testing to verify that 1.8.5/6 unpatched clients can continue to work with 2.1 servers (without 64bit_hash protocol support), excluding the NFS server issues.  If someone is exporting via NFS from a 2.1 NFS server it should be documented in the 2.1 release notes that they need to upgrade to a 2.1 client, or whatever else is needed to get the NFS server working properly.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
